YOUR TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES

The primary responsibilities of this role, Senior Biotech Data Scientist, are to:
Work with partners across the Biotech organization to turn data into critical information and knowledge for improved process understanding to facilitate data driven decisions making;
Query large sets of structured and unstructured data from disparate sources, clean and validate the data to ensure accuracy, completeness, and uniformity for analysis;
Perform advanced statistical analyses and data mining using state of the art methods, develop mathematical models to simulate biomanufacturing processes or cellular functions and behavior;
Develop stories and visualizations to effectively communicate complex analysis’ in clear, precise and actionable manner and work with data engineering teams to industrialize respective data science products;
Provide technical assessments based on statistics, data analysis and process knowledge, document findings and communicate to help partners understand and interpret results and recommendations;
Lead cross-functional teams and train junior data scientists;
Use own and leverage others business domain knowledge to design and scope studies and data analytics approaches and to determine appropriate statistics, algorithms, machine learning models, data sets and variables.

WHO YOU ARE

Your success will be driven by your demonstration of our LIFE values. More specifically related to this position, Bayer seeks an incumbent who possesses the following:

Required Qualifications:

Bachelor’s degree in Engineering or Science with at least eight years of relevant experience or master’s degree in Engineering or Science with at least four years of relevant experience or Ph.D. in Engineering or Science with at least two years of experience;
Able to independently develop and implement complex technical solutions and possesses strong critical thinking and problem-solving skills;
Demonstrates the ability to think creatively and takes initiative and can learn new technical topics and develop new technical skills quickly;
Possesses excellent oral and written communication skills and can clearly and effectively communicate complex concepts and data insights through the right medium in English;
Has experience with one or more programming languages such as Python, Java, R, MATLAB and respective programming tools such as gitlab, Jupyter, KNIME, SIMCA;
Has a strong background in fundamental, descriptive and inferential statistics and multivariate data analysis (MVDA) as well as experience with advanced analytical methods and techniques such as machine learning and takes delight in choosing the right statistical approaches and algorithms;
Has experience applying quantitative analyses (for example mathematical modeling, statistics and/or numerical analysis) for the improvement of processes;
Able to lead cross-functional project teams as a subject matter expert in process data analysis and statistics.

Preferred Qualifications:

Working knowledge of German language;
Experience in biological process development or manufacturing sciences environment with the use of design of experiments (DoE) and statistical data analysis;
Experience with visualization tools such as Tableau or Spotfire;
Experience in AWS cloud environment;
Knowledge of the regulatory environment in biotech / pharma.

